author: Chris Pleasance For Daily Mail Australia
title: Boy, 14, wrestles two-metre python from family's ute | Daily Mail Online
text: Share 441 shares A few moments later he can be heard saying 'I've got his head', before pulling out a huge reptile with his gloved fingers. Keeping a firm grip on the creature, he manages to scoot out from underneath the vehicle before plopping the animal into a bag. Oli gets himself upright before dropping the struggling snake into a bag to be relocated Oli's father, who goes by Chazza online, shakes hands with his son, bragging online that he's been wrestling snakes since age five The move is a fairly mean feat of strength for the young boy, as the python looks in no mood to go quietly. The whole incident was watched by a very proud dad, who goes by the name Chazza online. Posting the footage to Facebook, where it has attracted thousands of likes and shares, he wrote: 'That's my boy, been wrangling since he was five. 'Just a morning before school for him!'
